	(text_box "NOTE: TSMS has a resistance of ~3.2 Ohms across HVILS-A and HVILS-B, so with ~800 mA to 1A of current draw from the AIRs, the voltage drop is ~3V, so this circuit is put in place so the HVIL light isn't on when HVIL is actually closed correctly."
